snippet.textDisplay: I know exactly what you went through Joey! My Great Dane, Boxer, and Pitbull all went at each other and it was so scary and chaotic. It happened out of no where too, I was literally playing videos games! Everyone rushed out of their rooms to see what all the commotion was about and all we see are the dogs fighting recklessly. All 6 of us tried to help and separate them but it was extremely hard, our pit bull was close to a room so we tried to pull him in that direction to cut him off from the rest, he didn’t let go of the boxer, and my Great Dane didn’t let go of him so we had to start pouring salt in their eyes and start kicking their mouths to let go. He finally let go and we cut him from the fight and locked him into the room. We then continued with our Great Dane and boxer, 3 of us were on the Great Dane and 2 of us were on the boxer while my dad had his hands between their mouths to make them let go, I have no clue what he did but he probably shoved his hands up their throat to make them choke and to let go, as soon as that happened I’ve never pulled so hard in my life and rushed to the nearest room close to us. Finally it was over, the only main casualty’s was my dad’s hand, and my pit bulls back (he had to get surgery) we also don’t know how the fight started but they’re all okay now. Thank you for listening to my story, have a good day.
